TheoremW, there's no reason to post the key here as it is in the answer file (winnt.sif) and will be used automatically when you install by CD. However, if you're installing by hard drive then you'd run winnt32 /copysource:lang /dudisable /unattend:(winnt.sif or any name.txt)

Have a look at: Q dot GS/14lWh
Also: unattended. msfn. org/unattended. xp
BTW, if you're installing by hard drive, do the following before running winnt32:
Extract the .iso to a directory, copy+paste the OEM folder into $OEM$$1 (make a folder named $1).
Open the I386 folder, open DOSNET.INF and add these 2 lines under [Files]
d1,setuporg.exe
d1,presetup.cmd
Copy PRESETUP.CMD + SETUPORG.EXE from I386 and paste them into $OEM$$$System32
That's q[.]gs and unattended.msfn.org/unattended.xp
